mpm version 2.6-8 (2021-26)

Dependencies: ffmpeg, jq, mpv, socat, vim (any terminal text editor), yt-dlp.
Optionals but recommended: (
    dialog, fzf, mpvc, ncmpvc (use socat), GNU parallel,
    ranger (terminal file manager), ueberzug/ffmpegthumbnailer,
    w3m, ytfzf.
)

Youtube-dl is for now kind of unmaintained so install yt-dlp
https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp/releases
sudo pacman -S yt-dlp (it's just the continuation of youtube-dl).

This script reaps video urls from Youtube and so on. In our case we use ".m3u" files
to store urls and then be able to stream/download audio/videos from the site itself.
Converting .webm files is done using ffmpeg directly or through the parallel program.
We can save, remove, edit and schedule playlists. The mpm configuration file can also
be parse and edit during the session and changes will take effect immediately.

The installation script will create two configuration files (mpmrc,themerc)
as ~/.config/mpm/{mpmrc,themerc}, so please edit those files first and make sure
the directory names and structure are correctly set. The syntax is shell scripting.

